qas.question: Who are the six officials of The Order?

answers.text: Prelate; the Dean; the Secretary; the Registrar; the King of Arms; and the Usher

qas.question: Who serves as the Order's Prelate?

answers.text: The Bishop of London, a senior bishop in the Church of England

qas.question: Who was The Dean of St. Paul?

answers.text: ex officio the Dean of the Order

qas.question: Who is not a member of the College of Arms?
What is the Usher of the Order?

answers.text: Gentleman Usher of the Purple Rod

context: The Order has six officials: the <a0_0>Prelate; the Dean; the Secretary; the Registrar; the King of Arms; and the Usher<a0_0/>. <a1_0>The Bishop of London, a senior bishop in the Church of England<a1_0/>, serves as the Order's Prelate. The Dean of St Paul's is <a2_0>ex officio the Dean of the Order<a2_0/>. <a3_0>The Order's King of Arms<a3_0/> is not a member of the College of Arms, as are many other heraldic officers. The Usher of the Order is known as the <a4_0>Gentleman Usher of the Purple Rod<a4_0/>; he does not – unlike his Order of the Garter equivalent, the Gentleman Usher of the Black Rod – perform any duties related to the House of Lords.
